## Title
Beestgraph Knowledge Standard (BKS)

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Defines the BKS — the foundational specification unifying PARA, Zettelkasten, and Topic Trees into one interoperable standard enabling agent-to-agent knowledge exchange.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: evergreen" (Original insight about combining three methods into a unified standard. Represents personal design decisions — evergreen. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "meta/pkm, meta/workflows" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, meta/pkm" (BKS is fundamentally about beestgraph architecture. meta/beestgraph/architecture is more precise than meta/workflows.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to PARA Method, Zettelkasten Method, Topic Tree Organization, Content Types Taxonomy, Markdown Auto-Formatter, The Herd Protocol. BKS should also be a Concept node." (Central specification doc should be a hub node with many connections.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Status is qualifying — should be published. Missing created_at/updated_at dates. Summary is accurate.

